"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-brainstorm-2024-0722-1153478-olympic-games-hurling-gaelic-football\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Siobh\\u00e1n Doyle  Brainstorm  Analysis: rope climbing, underwater swimming, painting and sculpture are also sports which have disappeared from the Olympic Games over the years  TheOlympic Gamesis the largest sporting celebration for many reasons.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 243, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8, \"end\": 13, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arthur_Conan_Doyle\", \"score\": 0.9999999999790816, \"rank\": 2.071026211357009e-11, \"text\": \"Doyle\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arthur_Conan_Doyle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arthur_Conan_Doyle\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's because of the number of athletes present, the number of people from different nations gathered together in the same place at the same time and especially the vast number of sports on the schedule.\", \"from\": 244, \"to\": 446, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But sincethe first modern Olympic Games in 1896, many sports have disappeared completely from the schedule.\", \"from\": 447, \"to\": 554, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What sports are no longer played at Olympic level - and why?\", \"from\": 555, \"to\": 615, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"TheInternational Olympic Committeemakes decisions about which sports are included in the Olympic Games and which are omitted.\", \"from\": 617, \"to\": 742, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The postponedTokyo 2020 Olympicshad 339 events\\u00a0scheduled in 33 different sports for both men and women.\", \"from\": 743, \"to\": 846, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, this has not always been the case, as women were subject to restrictions ever since they made their Olympic debut in 1900.\", \"from\": 848, \"to\": 979, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Women were initially restricted to compete in the tennis and golf competitions and, over the course of the next century, they gained access to more Olympic sports.\", \"from\": 980, \"to\": 1143, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was not until the 2012 Games in London,with the introduction of women's boxing, that women could compete in all the sports on the schedule.\", \"from\": 1144, \"to\": 1286, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1179, \"end\": 1185, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_GAA\", \"score\": 0.9993355950395445, \"rank\": 0.0006648466797506518, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_GAA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_GAA\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This proved to be a welcome addition for Ireland's Olympic endeavors, asKatie Taylor picked up a gold medalat the inaugural women's boxing event.\", \"from\": 1287, \"to\": 1432, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1328, \"end\": 1335, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999999988340278, \"rank\": 1.1660075366269878e-09, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We need your consent to load this rte-player contentWe use rte-player to manage extra content that can set cookies on your device and collect data about your activity.\", \"from\": 1434, \"to\": 1601, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please review their details and accept them to load the content.Manage Preferences  From RT\\u00c9 Radio 1's Morning Ireland,\\u00a0Darren Frehill recalls Katie Taylor's gold medal at the Olympic Games in 2012  In the early years of the Olympic Games,rope climbingfeatured as part of the gymnastics program.\", \"from\": 1602, \"to\": 1897, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1745, \"end\": 1757, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Taylor\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Taylor\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Taylor\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Taylor\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Competitors would start from a seated position before attempting to climb the 25ft vertical rope.\", \"from\": 1898, \"to\": 1995, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The event disappeared from the Games in 1932 and nowadays only\\u00a0features when people are competing for the title ofIreland's Fittest Family.\", \"from\": 1996, \"to\": 2135, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Basque Pelotais perhaps one of the most obscure of lost Olympics sports, as the only time is was part of the Olympics was in 1900 in Paris.\", \"from\": 2137, \"to\": 2276, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2137, \"end\": 2143, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Basque_language\", \"score\": 0.989621462476562, \"rank\": 0.0104829686871331, \"text\": \"Basque\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Basque_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Basque_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2270, \"end\": 2275, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999745341, \"rank\": 2.550109013626974e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This ancient game from Spain can be played with a hand, racket or a basket on the wrist and the ball is smashed against a wall.\", \"from\": 2277, \"to\": 2404, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2300, \"end\": 2305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9998756499381168, \"rank\": 0.00012435430267376672, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only two teams competed, so only one match was ever played.\", \"from\": 2405, \"to\": 2464, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Spain won, making themthe first and last Olympic champions of the sport.\", \"from\": 2465, \"to\": 2537, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2465, \"end\": 2470, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9998756499381168, \"rank\": 0.00012435430267376672, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From British Path\\u00e9, a 1933 introduction to Basque Pelota  Inspired by theGAA World Games, in which various clubs across the world gathered to play during a week-long tournament, GAA president Liam O'Neillsaidin 2014 that there were plans to seek official Olympic status for our national games However, Gaelic football and hurling madea brief appearance in the 1904 Olympicsin an unofficial capacity whenFenians FC from Chicago beat host team St Louisby ten goals to nil.\", \"from\": 2541, \"to\": 3011, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2546, \"end\": 2559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Path\\u00e9_News\", \"score\": 0.8835314487922844, \"rank\": 0.13182025058897365, \"text\": \"British Path\\u00e9\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Path\\u00e9_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Path\\u00e9_News\"}, {\"begin\": 2584, \"end\": 2590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Basque_language\", \"score\": 0.989621462476562, \"rank\": 0.0104829686871331, \"text\": \"Basque\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Basque_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Basque_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2719, \"end\": 2732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_the_Gaelic_Athletic_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"GAA president\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_the_Gaelic_Athletic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_the_Gaelic_Athletic_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 2733, \"end\": 2737, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liam_Gallagher\", \"score\": 0.9999999632100305, \"rank\": 3.6732177852867947e-08, \"text\": \"Liam\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liam_Gallagher\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liam_Gallagher\"}, {\"begin\": 2960, \"end\": 2967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\", \"score\": 0.9959329288682068, \"rank\": 0.004083108941683221, \"text\": \"Chicago\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Baseball was added as an official Olympic sport in 1992, with its sister sport softball joining in four years later for the Games in Atlanta.\", \"from\": 3013, \"to\": 3154, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3146, \"end\": 3153, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.83979844485002e-15, \"text\": \"Atlanta\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2012, however, both were dropped from the Olympic ticket, the first time in 69 years that a sport itself had been removed from the Olympic program since\\u00a0polo was pushed out in 1936.\", \"from\": 3155, \"to\": 3339, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Professional baseball players had been allowed to compete in the Olympics, but often refused to compete due to an overlap with the Major League Baseball season.\", \"from\": 3341, \"to\": 3501, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3472, \"end\": 3493, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Major_League_Baseball\", \"score\": 0.9999927413677738, \"rank\": 6.7554211644703174e-06, \"text\": \"Major League Baseball\", \"types\": [\"Q6631808\", \"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Major_League_Baseball\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Major_League_Baseball\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC cited the League's unwillingness to alter its season as a significant factor for dropping both sports.\", \"from\": 3502, \"to\": 3612, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3506, \"end\": 3509, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.183615852042158e-39, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the snub was short lived and both baseball and softball weredue to returnto Olympic sport status for the 2020 Tokyo Games.\", \"from\": 3613, \"to\": 3744, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"From Facts, Irish dudes watch baseball for the first time  In Ancient Greece, art and sport were seen as perfect partners and this ideal was adopted for the modern Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 3748, \"to\": 3926, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3760, \"end\": 3765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9998104524450124, \"rank\": 0.00018876556435043352, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1912,architecture, sculpture, painting, literature and music competitionswere part of the Olympic Games.Ireland's first Olympic medalswere secured at the 1924 Paris Games for painting\\u00a0and literature: Jack Butler Yeats won silver for his paintingThe Liffey Swimand Oliver St John Gogarty won bronze in literature for hisOde to the Tailteann Games.\", \"from\": 3927, \"to\": 4276, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4130, \"end\": 4147, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Butler_Yeats\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jack Butler Yeats\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Butler_Yeats\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Butler_Yeats\"}, {\"begin\": 4194, \"end\": 4216, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oliver_St._John_Gogarty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Oliver St John Gogarty\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oliver_St._John_Gogarty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oliver_St._John_Gogarty\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ireland returned to the medal podium in art contests at the 1948 London Games whenLetitia Hamilton took bronze in paintingfor herMeath Hunt Point-to-Point Racesoil painting.\", \"from\": 4277, \"to\": 4450, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4277, \"end\": 4284, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999999988340278, \"rank\": 1.1660075366269878e-09, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 4367, \"end\": 4375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamilton_Academical_F.C.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.923619850124421e-28, \"text\": \"Hamilton\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamilton_Academical_F.C.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamilton_Academical_F.C.\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This would be Ireland's last Olympic medal in such events as the arts and culture categories were discontinued in 1948.\", \"from\": 4452, \"to\": 4571, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4466, \"end\": 4473, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999999988340278, \"rank\": 1.1660075366269878e-09, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These competitions were replaced with cultural programmes which\\u00a0were completely separate from the sports competitions.\", \"from\": 4572, \"to\": 4690, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Artists, designers, architects, choreographers and musicians now play an active part in the success of the Games in the construction of stadiums and other competition venues, the design of logos and mascots and the all-important spectacles of the opening and closing ceremonies.\", \"from\": 4691, \"to\": 4969, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"From the Olympic Channel, some of the forgotten events from past Olympics  With all of these additions and exclusions in mind, what are the criteria for the addition of a sport to the prestigious Games?\", \"from\": 4973, \"to\": 5175, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4982, \"end\": 4997, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Channel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.456028591897674e-27, \"text\": \"Olympic Channel\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Channel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Channel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Firstly, sporting events are added, discontinued and sometimes reintroduced at Olympic level on the basis of their international popularity.Underwater swimmingwas scrapped from the Olympic schedule due to a lack of public appeal.\", \"from\": 5176, \"to\": 5405, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Held in the River Seine during the 1900 Games in Paris, 14 swimmers from four\\u00a0nations took part.\", \"from\": 5406, \"to\": 5502, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5418, \"end\": 5429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 5455, \"end\": 5460, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999745341, \"rank\": 2.550109013626974e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Competitors were awarded two points for each metre swum underwater and one point for each second that they stayed under water.\", \"from\": 5503, \"to\": 5629, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For a sport to contested at Olympic level, it has to be governed by an international federation recognised by the International Olympic Committee.\", \"from\": 5631, \"to\": 5777, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5745, \"end\": 5776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sadly, this rules outbubble soccer, samba hurling and bog snorkelingbecoming Olympic sports for the foreseeable.\", \"from\": 5778, \"to\": 5890, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The views expressed here are those of the author and do not represent or reflect the views of RT\\u00c9  Brainstorm  Follow@thekickart  \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026.\", \"from\": 5892, \"to\": 6033, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5986, \"end\": 5989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"score\": 0.9835080667082595, \"rank\": 0.013767790549921992, \"text\": \"RT\\u00c9\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/res